ular muscles such as around eye and mouth.<\/p>\n\n<p>The reason why I am wondering is because in biology normally nothing is ever just like that, there is always an exception. This would be the first biological rule without exception that I came across.<\/p>\n\n<p>I am thinking of humans only for a start but feel free to include any other animal if any have skeletal muscles without antagonists :)<\/p>\n","question_id":2373,"tags":["muscles","anatomy"],"score":7,"accepted_answer_id":2377,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":579,"up_vote_count":7,"last_edit_date":1337900666},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d2ecbadc57c0e7692ff27ec985b64af0?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":839,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/839/odp","reputation":240,"display_name":"ODP","accept_rate":25},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/49e94b363348f897f337a5bce2beec20?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":68,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/68/marta-cz-c","reputation":1717,"display_name":"Marta Cz-C","accept_rate":50},"score":0,"post_id":2367,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337800382,"comment_id":3226,"body":"I love the subject of experimental evolution! Give me some time and I&#39;ll write more about it."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d2ecbadc57c0e7692ff27ec985b64af0?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":839,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/839/odp","reputation":240,"display_name":"ODP","accept_rate":25},"score":0,"post_id":2367,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/49e94b363348f897f337a5bce2beec20?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":68,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/68/marta-cz-c","reputation":1717,"display_name":"Marta Cz-C","accept_rate":50},"edited":false,"creation_date":1337876235,"comment_id":3251,"body":"It is one of the most amazing things"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/08613e0b782cdf2bb8f2501cae9bdc5d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":806,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/806/armatus","reputation":5317,"display_name":"Armatus","accept_rate":81},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/49e94b363348f897f337a5bce2beec20?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":68,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/68/marta-cz-c","reputation":1717,"display_name":"Marta Cz-C","accept_rate":50},"score":3,"post_id":2370,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337800209,"comment_id":3225,"body":"Quite discouraging. As far as I know one don&#39;t need very expensive equipment to experiment with natural selection (especially among fruit fly!). Creativity and a lot of patience would be much more needed."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/08613e0b782cdf2bb8f2501cae9bdc5d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":806,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/806/armatus","reputation":5317,"display_name":"Armatus","accept_rate":81},"score":0,"post_id":2370,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/49e94b363348f897f337a5bce2beec20?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":68,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/68/marta-cz-c","reputation":1717,"display_name":"Marta Cz-C","accept_rate":50},"edited":false,"creation_date":1337802538,"comment_id":3227,"body":"I&#39;m not aware of what experiment they carried out there so I wrote my answer trying to stay on the safe side, assuming that it was a full-out scientific project :) Of course, experimenting is well possible on a small scale especially with these little ones."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d2ecbadc57c0e7692ff27ec985b64af0?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"reg