ible to maintain high enough a competition of parasites without that defensive mechanism to prevent the ones with the mechanism from developing. It's natural selection at work :)<\/p>\n","answer_id":2337,"question_id":2335,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/2335/how-do-susceptible-organisms-prevent-parasites-from-overcoming-resistance","last_activity_date":1337648919,"creation_date":1337630338,"answer_count":1,"title":"How do susceptible organisms prevent parasites from overcoming resistance?","body":"<p>Bt corn is genetically modified to kill borers, but \"regulations require farmers to plant conventional varieties as well, which is intended to stop the borers becoming resistant.\"\n-<a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-11496710\" rel=\"nofollow\">Source<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>How do susceptible organisms prevent parasites from overcoming host resistance? <\/p>\n","question_id":2335,"tags":["ecology"],"score":3,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":110,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1337648919},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5cff3e84bcedd40163c74d33b827ac7c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/307/lancelafontaine","reputation":3814,"display_name":"LanceLafontaine","accept_rate":47},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5cff3e84bcedd40163c74d33b827ac7c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/307/lancelafontaine","reputation":3814,"display_name":"LanceLafontaine","accept_rate":47},"score":0,"post_id":2270,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337104137,"comment_id":3022,"body":"I realize that this question isn&#39;t exactly &quot;precise&quot;, and I might be using the wrong terminology. Feel free to edit or let me know how I can improve the question."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/ava