that have to change too - the chemical reactions in the cell will go haywire when temperature changes too, so lots of genes must make adjustment for a fully cold adapted plant.  <\/p>\n","answer_id":2285,"question_id":1964,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/1964/why-are-some-plants-frost-tender","last_activity_date":1337192401,"creation_date":1335320328,"answer_count":1,"title":"Why are some plants frost tender?","body":"<p>Why do some plants have the ability to stand frost, while others can't? Does it have to do with the size of the water vacuoles in the plant cells?<\/p>\n","question_id":1964,"tags":["botany","plant-physiology"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":2285,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":79,"up_vote_count":5},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/222b478bab6d59dc5de514a87dba88cd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":389,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/389/bobthejoe","reputation":4911,"display_name":"bobthejoe","accept_rate":53},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/13f5a730dead005d0a3a947d3c09ab81?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":691,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/691/chm","reputation":553,"display_name":"CHM"},"score":4,"post_id":1245,"edited":false,"creation_date":1333421241,"comment_id":2066,"body":"Excellent question for the upcoming Chemistry beta. This should be moved once the proposal reaches beta."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/222b478bab6d59dc5de514a87dba88cd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":389,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/389/bobthejoe","reputation":4911,"display_name":"bobthejoe","accept_rate":53},"score":1,"post_id":1245,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/13f5a730dead005d0a3a947d3c09ab81?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":691,"link"