swimming for \"terrestrial\" bird seems much more straightforward.<\/p>\n","answer_id":2163,"question_id":2137,"up_vote_count":6}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/2137/did-we-first-have-swimming-birds-or-flying-birds","last_activity_date":1336384722,"creation_date":1336330911,"answer_count":2,"title":"Did we first have swimming birds or flying birds?","body":"<p>Looking at the swimming birds building nests just across my garden, I suddenly wondered how evolution came to swimming birds and whether flying birds started swimming or whether swimming bird like animals started flying.<\/p>\n\n<p>What came first and when and why?<\/p>\n","question_id":2137,"tags":["evolution","ornithology"],"score":12,"accepted_answer_id":2155,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":291,"up_vote_count":12},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/75ac58e3e0106650994b315a6ad4c525?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":103,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/103/inquilinekea","reputation":1084,"display_name":"InquilineKea","accept_rate":52},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/08613e0b782cdf2bb8f2501cae9bdc5d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":806,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/806/armatus","reputation":5317,"display_name":"Armatus","accept_rate":81},"score":1,"post_id":2135,"edited":false,"creation_date":1336340195,"comment_id":2838,"body":"You can find this on Wikipedia: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolution_of_flagella#Symbiotic.2Fendosymbiotic.2Fexogenous_models\" rel=\"nofollow\">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/&hellip;<\/a>. In lectures we have also been made aware of the fused membrane of cilia with the cell rather than the separate membranes of endosymbionts. There were more (better) reasons but I&#39;ve forgotten."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fdd630f72eef3790bfb4ef38d08c7f85?s=128&d=iden